#### Getting the Original Source IP Address through a Reverse Proxy

In [[NGINX]], its done like this:

<pre class="sh_sh">
proxy_set_header X-Forwarded-For $proxy_add_x_forwarded_for;
</pre>

In [[Lighttpd]], its done like this:

<pre class="sh_sh">
extforward.forwarder = ("10.0.0.232" => "trust")
</pre>

The trust factor here involves matching the ip of the trusted proxies.

Same goes for [[Apache2]] [[Rpaf]]:

<pre class="sh_xml">
&lt;IfModule mod_rpaf.c>
RPAFenable On
RPAFsethostname Off
RPAFproxy_ips 127.0.0.1 192.168.8.2
&lt;/IfModule>
</pre>

